<DocsLayout title="Community" description="Join the Portefaix community and learn how to contribute.">
  <p class="doc-eyebrow">// community</p>

  <h1>Community</h1>

  <p>
    Portefaix is an open-source project built by platform engineers for platform engineers.
    All development happens in the open on GitHub, and contributions of any size are welcome.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Get Involved</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>GitHub</strong> — Browse code, open issues, and submit pull requests at
      <a href="https://github.com/portefaix" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/portefaix</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Issues</strong> — Found a bug or have a feature request? Open an issue on the relevant
      sub-project repository.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Discussions</strong> — Ask questions and share ideas in GitHub Discussions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Pull Requests</strong> — All contributions are reviewed and merged via pull requests.
      See the <a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-kubernetes/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contributing Guide</a>
      for details.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Repositories</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Repository</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-kubernetes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">portefaix-kubernetes</a></td>
        <td>Kubernetes platform configurations and GitOps stacks</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-infrastructure" target="_blank" rel="noopener">portefaix-infrastructure</a></td>
        <td>Terraform modules and cloud infrastructure</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-hub" target="_blank" rel="noopener">portefaix-hub</a></td>
        <td>Helm chart registry</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="https://github.com/portefaix/portefaix-policies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">portefaix-policies</a></td>
        <td>Policy library (Kyverno + OPA)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>

  <p>
    Portefaix follows the
    <a href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct
    </a>.
    We expect all participants to adhere to it in all project spaces.
  </p>

  <h2>License</h2>

  <p>
    All Portefaix sub-projects are licensed under the
    <a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apache License 2.0</a>.
    Contributions are accepted under the same license via the Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO).
  </p>

  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>First contribution?</strong> Look for issues tagged <code>good first issue</code> on any
      of the sub-project repositories — they're specifically chosen for new contributors.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
